The people of western Guangdong Province in southern China have their own way of ushering in the Chinese New Year â€“ with chicken! This delicious and nutritious bird has an auspicious significance on banquet tables in this part of China. Lei Kalin, the head chef of a Cantonese restaurant, cooks thousands of servings of chicken every Chinese New Year. Whether boiled or steamed, delicately cooked chicken always symbolizes good luck and happiness for the upcoming year!